.TH smi-selenium-node "1" "October 2025" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Selenium Command"
.SH NAME
smi-selenium-node \- Start a Selenium Grid Node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-selenium-node
.I HUB_URL
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B smi-selenium-node
starts a Selenium Grid Node and registers it with the Hub at the specified \fIHUB_URL\fR.
It uses the Selenium standalone JAR file found in the SMI library location.
It requires the \fBSELENIUM_JAR_FILE_NAME\fR environment variable to be set to the name of the Selenium JAR file.
.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Command written by Imre Tabur.
Documentation written by Imre Tabur.
